Instructions how to build the PyGTK-Installer for Inkscape

1. Create a directory with the name "files"
2. Create a directory with the name "build"
3. Populate the directory "files" with the PyGTK source files. 
   These files can be found under Donwloads of the TexText repository.
   Make sure you choose the correct version (Inkscape 0.91 -> Python 2.6,
   Inkscape 0.92 -> Python 2.7)
   After this operation the files directory should contain four subdirectories:
   inlcude, Lib, Scripts, and share
4. Compile the installer script installer_pygtk_inkscape_0.9x using 
   nullsoft scriptable install system 3.01
5. You will find the package in the build directory.